comment.body: Synopsis: In the final days of the reign of Marcus Aurelius (Richard Harris), the emperor arouses the wrath of his son Commodus (Joaquin Phoenix) by making public his predilection to leave the throne to Maximus (Russell Crowe), the commander of the Roman army. Hungry for power, Commodus kills his father, takes the crown and orders the death of Maximus, who manages to flee before being caught and goes into hiding under the identity of a Roman Empire slave and gladiator.

Synopsis: In the near future, Thomas Anderson (Keanu Reeves), a young computer programmer who lives in a dark cubicle, is plagued by strange nightmares in which he finds himself wired against his will in a huge computer system of the future. On all these occasions, he wakes up screaming just as the electrodes are about to penetrate his brain. As the dream repeats itself, Anderson begins to have doubts about reality. Through an encounter with the mysterious Morpheus (Laurence Fishburne) and Trinity (Carrie-Anne Moss), Thomas discovers that he is, like other people, a victim of the Matrix, an intelligent and artificial system that manipulates people's minds, creating illusion of a real world while using the brains and bodies of individuals to produce energy. Morpheus, however, is convinced that Thomas is Neo, the long-awaited messiah capable of confronting the Matrix and leading people back to reality and freedom.
